	"id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000d3d5691e",
	"advisoryNumber": "ADV236618",
	"advisoryType": "SecurityAdvisory",
	"body": "<div style=\"margin:0px;clear:both;cursor:text;\"><p style=\"margin:0px;font-weight:normal;color:windowtext;text-align:left;\"><span lang=EN-US style=\"margin:0px;color:rgb(36, 36, 36);font-weight:bold;\"><span style=\"margin:0px;\"></span></span> </p><div style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Web&quot;, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif;font-size:12px;margin:0px;clear:both;font-weight:400;text-align:start;\"><h1 style=\"margin:0px;font-weight:normal;color:windowtext;text-align:left;\"><span lang=EN-US style=\"margin:0px;color:rgb(36, 36, 36);font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_EmbeddedFont&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_MSCustomFont&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_MSFontService&quot;, sans-serif;font-weight:bold;\"><span style=\"margin:0px;\"><h1 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:600;text-align:start;\"> </h1></span></span> </h1> </div> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;margin:0px;clear:both;\"><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Web&quot;, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif;font-size:12px;margin:0px;clear:both;\"><h1 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:normal;margin:0px;color:windowtext;text-align:left;\"><span lang=EN-US style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;color:rgb(36, 36, 36);font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_EmbeddedFont&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_MSCustomFont&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_MSFontService&quot;, sans-serif;font-weight:bold;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;\"><h1 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:600;text-align:start;\">General Information&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">&nbsp;</span> </h1></span></span> </h1> </div> </div><h2 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Executive Summary </h2><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Microsoft is aware of<span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;cursor:pointer;\"><u><a href=\"https://www.amd.com/en/resources/product-security/bulletin/amd-sb-7033.html\">AMD-SB-7033/CVE-2024-36347</a></u></span><span>&nbsp;</span>disclosed by AMD on March 5, 2025. Microsoft is not aware of any active attacks leveraging this vulnerability.</span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">This vulnerability requires local administrator privileges to load malicious microcode. Mitigations are in place across all Microsoft cloud services. As a result, Microsoft cloud customers are already protected and no customer action is required.</span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">To further protect against this vulnerability, we are actively applying AMD’s update to all of our internal AMD-based systems and deploying a BIOS update which may require a reboot. If customers are required to perform a reboot due to the BIOS update, they will be notified via Azure Service Health. &nbsp;<br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div><h2 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Advisory FAQ </h2><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><b style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Why is this AMD CVE included in the Security Update Guide?</b> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\">The vulnerability assigned to<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.cve.org/CVERecord/SearchResults?query=CVE-2024-36347\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;text-decoration:underline;cursor:pointer;\">CVE-2024-36347</a><span>&nbsp;</span>affects some processor models offered by AMD. This MSRC Advisory was published to inform customers of the actions Microsoft has taken to protect against the vulnerability. &nbsp; </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\">&nbsp; </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\">Please see the following for more information on this vulnerability from AMD:&nbsp; </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><ul style=\"box-sizing:border-box;padding:0px 0px 0px 40px;\"><li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;cursor:pointer;\"><u><a href=\"https://www.amd.com/en/resources/product-security/bulletin/amd-sb-7033.html\">AMD-SB-7033</a></u></span> </li> </ul><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><b style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_EmbeddedFont&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_MSFontService&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;text-align:left;\">Are Microsoft<span>&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_EmbeddedFont&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_MSFontService&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;text-align:left;\">cloud services, including<span>&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_EmbeddedFont&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_MSFontService&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;text-align:left;\">Microsoft<span>&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_EmbeddedFont&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_MSFontService&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;text-align:left;\">Azure and M</span><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_EmbeddedFont&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_MSFontService&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;text-align:left;\">icrosoft<span>&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_EmbeddedFont&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_MSFontService&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;text-align:left;\">365,<span>&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_EmbeddedFont&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI_MSFontService&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;text-align:left;\">protected</span>?</b><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Mitigations are in place across all Microsoft cloud services and Microsoft cloud customers are already protected.</span></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span></span><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">As an additional protection, we are deploying the AMD microcode update to all affected systems in our fleet and deploying a BIOS update to these systems, which may require a reboot.</span></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><b style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">How will customers be notified if a reboot is required for the BIOS update when it becomes available? </b></span></span><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">The Azure Service Health Portal. More info is available here: <a href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-gb/azure/virtual-machines/maintenance-notifications-portal\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;text-decoration:underline;cursor:pointer;\">Use the portal for maintenance notifications - Azure Virtual Machines | Microsoft Learn</a>. <br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><b style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">How does this vulnerability affect cloud services?</b><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">This vulnerability impacts AMD-based hardware hosting cloud services. A malicious actor with local administrator privileges on the target could load malicious microcode. However, we have already deployed mitigations to prevent exploitation and are not aware of any attacks leveraging this vulnerability.</span><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">&nbsp;<b style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Are guest Virtual Machines (VMs) impacted?</b><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div>No. All Microsoft cloud customers, including Azure customers with virtual machines (VMs) are protected. No customer action is required.<br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><b style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></b></span><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><b style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Is there any action Microsoft Azure, Microsoft 365, or Microsoft consumer and commercial cloud customers need to take?</b><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">No.</span><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><b style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Is there any action for Windows client or Windows server customers?</b> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Customers should contact their hardware provider (OEM) for information on steps taken to mitigate the AMD vulnerability.<br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><b style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Are Microsoft Surface Devices affected by this vulnerability?</b> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Surface Laptop 4s with AMD Ryzen chips are affected by AMD-SB-7033/CVE-2024-36347. We are working with AMD to enable the fix in a future update which will be available through a Windows Update. See <a href=\"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/surface/surface-update-history-6036fff5-edec-c8ec-9796-a5633aac9488\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;text-decoration:underline;cursor:pointer;\">Surface update history</a> for more information.<br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div>If you wish to install the updates manually, you can do the following:</span><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><ol style=\"box-sizing:border-box;padding-left:40px;\"><li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">In the Surface app, expand <b style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Help &amp; support</b> to check the update status.</span> </li><li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">If there are updates available, select the <b style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Check for updates</b> button to open Windows Update and install the available updates.</span> </li> </ol> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:600;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Disclaimer</span> </h3><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">The information provided in this advisory is provided &quot;as is&quot; without warranty of any kind. Microsoft disclaims all warranties, either express or implied, including the warranties of merchantability and fitness for a particular purpose. In no event shall Microsoft Corporation or its suppliers be liable for any damages whatsoever including direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, loss of business profits or special damages, even if Microsoft Corporation or its suppliers have been advised of the possibility of such damages. Some states do not allow the exclusion or limitation of liability for consequential or incidental damages so the foregoing limitation may not apply.</span> </div> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> </div></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:600;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Revisions</span> </h3><ul style=\"box-sizing:border-box;padding:0px 0px 0px 40px;\"><li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">V1.0 (March 5, 2025): Advisory published.</span> </li> </ul> </div><div><ul> </ul> </div><div style=\"margin:0px;clear:both;cursor:text;\"><div style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Web&quot;, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif;font-size:12px;margin:0px;clear:both;text-align:start;\"><h2 style=\"margin:0px;color:windowtext;text-align:left;\"><span>&nbsp;</span><br> </h2> </div> </div>",
